-- TABLE-Brazil's IGP-M price index soars in March
-- By Silvio Cascione
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 07:16AM EDT
-- None



BRASILIA, March 28 (Reuters) - Brazil's broadest price index, the IGP-M <BRIGP=ECI>, rose 1.67 percent in March from the previous month, private think tank Getulio Vargas Foundation said on Friday.

The index had been expected to rise 1.55 percent, according to the median forecast of 28 economists polled by Reuters. In the 12 months through June, the IGP-M index rose 7.30 percent, up from 5.76 percent in the previous month.